THE ENERGETIC. M. & J. TRACY, Inc., v. UNITED STATES. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. January 25, 1924.) No. 189. Park, Mattison & Lynch, of New York City (Samuel Park and Anthony V. Lynch, Jr., both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee Tice Towing Line. Balph C. Greene, U. S. Atty., of Brooklyn, N. Y., and Horace M. Gray, Sp. Asst. U. S. Atty., of New York City (Glen B. Snider, Admiralty Counsel, U. S. Shipping Board, of New York City, of counsel), for the United States.

Before BOGEBS, MANTON, and MAYEB, Circuit Judges.

PEB OUBIAM.

Decree affirmed.
